## GUI Configuration — {{ script.title }}
## Generated by VN-Agent
##
## Design principles (user brief, Sprint 12-3d):
##   1. Readability first — gradient panel at bottom, not a hard rectangle;
##      gentle top fade so BG/sprite breathes through; line-height 1.6×.
##   2. Speaker identity — name tag floats ABOVE the textbox in its own
##      pill; speaker color comes from the Character(color=...) define.
##   3. Pacing — typewriter with punctuation-aware pauses; CTC arrow at
##      bottom-right pulses when Ren'Py is waiting for a click.
##   4. Diegetic minimum — no heavy chrome; backdrop is the speaker's
##      own color tint at very low alpha, so the UI feels theme-aware
##      without a bespoke frame per genre.

init python:
    config.name = "{{ script.title }}"
    config.version = "1.0"
    config.window_title = "{{ script.title }}"

## ── Layout ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
define gui.textbox_height = 300
define gui.textbox_yalign = 1.0
define gui.textbox_xpadding = 180
define gui.textbox_ypadding_top = 70
define gui.textbox_ypadding_bottom = 50

## Textbox backdrop — a vertical gradient (transparent at top, ~85%
## opaque at bottom). Built from a stack of two Solid layers inside a
## Fixed so the alpha ramp is cheap to render. Ren'Py's im.MatrixColor
## could do a true gradient but this two-step approximation is good
## enough at 1920x1080 and avoids a runtime matrix multiply per frame.
image textbox_bg = Composite(
    (1920, 300),
    (0, 0),   Solid("#0a0f1466", xsize=1920, ysize=80),
    (0, 80),  Solid("#0a0f14b0", xsize=1920, ysize=80),
    (0, 160), Solid("#0a0f14d8", xsize=1920, ysize=140),
)

